1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:00,960
What about us?

2
00:00:01,320 --> 00:00:02,520
Are we dating?

3
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:05,440
What should we call each other?

4
00:00:05,760 --> 00:00:07,960
My number is saved as Orange.

5
00:00:08,080 --> 00:00:09,200
Your number is saved as Orange’s owner.

6
00:00:10,640 --> 00:00:13,600
Will Tle choose to attend med school like Ko Song?

7
00:00:13,960 --> 00:00:15,400
Aren’t you worried about being apart from him?

8
00:00:15,840 --> 00:00:16,400
Ko Song.

9
00:00:16,760 --> 00:00:18,000
After we graduate from high school,

10
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:19,880
will you leave me?

11
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:22,520
Even though we like different things,

12
00:00:23,120 --> 00:00:24,680
it doesn’t mean we will go separate ways.

13
00:00:25,280 --> 00:00:25,840
Don’t argue with me.

14
00:00:26,280 --> 00:00:26,960
If you do, I’ll kiss you.

15
00:00:32,520 --> 00:00:35,000
(I always remember the atmosphere before we graduated high school.)

16
00:00:35,560 --> 00:00:39,280
(It was the time when we were forced to grow up.)

17
00:00:40,280 --> 00:00:42,640
(It was the time we began to fear)

18
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:44,680
(that if we didn’t study hard,)

19
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:46,680
(we might be the only ones who didn’t get into college.)

20
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:52,680
(Everything that used to be simple, it suddenly became hard.)

21
00:00:53,840 --> 00:00:55,720
(The entrance exam was approaching.)

22
00:00:57,640 --> 00:01:00,520
(We needed to stop playing around.)

23
00:01:03,520 --> 00:01:04,520
You need to study.

24
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:05,360
The exam is coming soon.

25
00:01:06,120 --> 00:01:07,160
Sorry.

26
00:01:07,240 --> 00:01:08,040
What did you say?

27
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:16,400
(Even I, Boss Ko, had to give in to the educational system.)

28
00:03:31,280 --> 00:03:33,240
You will take the entrance exam soon.

29
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:38,120
I want you to think about whether your interest is still the same.

30
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:41,080
If you’re still going to choose the same faculty,

31
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:42,200
show me your hand.

32
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:47,520
Okay, you can put your hand down.

33
00:03:48,640 --> 00:03:52,000
Choosing the faculty is important.

34
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:56,920
Do you think universities in Bangkok are better?

35
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:59,960
I don’t think so.

36
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:06,680
You should choose a university based on
the curriculum and the living environment.

37
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:10,520
How about this? Close your eyes.

38
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:15,360
Imagine your college life.

39
00:04:31,440 --> 00:04:33,160
Did you imagine you were living in Bangkok?

40
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:35,040
Yes.

41
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:39,040
The thought of living in the city already gives me chills.

42
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:41,760
Are you only considering schools close to home?

43
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:45,000
If I can choose, I want to be close to home.

44
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:47,640
If I live away,

45
00:04:48,360 --> 00:04:50,760
my mom won’t be able to live.

46
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,960
Okay, open your eyes.

47
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:59,840
Do the test and see if the result matches
the faculty that you want to choose.

48
00:05:00,120 --> 00:05:00,720
Do it.

49
00:05:08,960 --> 00:05:10,320
Which university do you plan to attend?

50
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,240
I’m not sure.

51
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:20,800
I’ll attend any university that I get into.

52
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:45,360
Why didn’t you wake me up?

53
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,520
I saw you sleeping soundly. I didn’t want to wake you up.

54
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:55,520
Hey.

55
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:57,440
Today is Saturday.

56
00:05:58,440 --> 00:05:59,960
Why don’t we buy a comic book to read?

57
00:06:01,160 --> 00:06:03,680
You should be studying. You didn’t study last night.

58
00:06:04,800 --> 00:06:07,880
But I’ve been studying with you for over a month.

59
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,680
Can I have a break?

60
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:12,120
You are smart.

61
00:06:12,280 --> 00:06:13,440
I’m sure you can get into college.

62
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,560
Don’t be careless.

63
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:17,880
Students from other schools are also smart.

64
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:19,480
You’re so boring.

65
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,320
Can we go in the evening?

66
00:06:29,960 --> 00:06:31,120
We can ask our friends to go have snacks.

67
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,240
It’s okay.

68
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,320
You should go back to your study.

69
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:40,400
I’ll ask August to go with me.

70
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,400
You’re so cold.

71
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:52,960
I feel lonely, but you refuse to hang out with me.

72
00:06:53,880 --> 00:06:56,360
(So who would help my mom buy groceries?)

73
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,840
(Augar went to basketball practice since early this morning.)

74
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,600
Achi is definitely with Augar.

75
00:07:04,880 --> 00:07:07,000
Why is no one free this weekend?

76
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,440
(What is Ko Song doing?)

77
00:07:10,920 --> 00:07:11,760
(Let me guess.)

78
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:13,040
(He’s studying.)

79
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:15,520
Yeah.

80
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:17,520
All he does is study all day.

81
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:19,600
How can he do that?

82
00:07:20,760 --> 00:07:22,160
(He wants to go to med school.)

83
00:07:22,720 --> 00:07:23,440
(It’s not easy to get in.)

84
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:24,760
(You should be more understanding.)

85
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,840
You nag me just like my mom did.

86
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:30,280
I’m going to take a shower.

87
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:31,200
I’m hanging up.

88
00:07:47,280 --> 00:07:49,680
Teenagers these days are unpredictable.

89
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:55,000
They can quickly go from having fun
to feeling lonely, hungry, or sleepy.

90
00:08:01,480 --> 00:08:01,800
Uncle.

91
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:02,920
What?

92
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:04,520
What degree do you have?

93
00:08:05,440 --> 00:08:07,400
Which college did you attend?

94
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,320
I didn’t even attend middle school.

95
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,080
I only attended elementary school.

96
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:14,640
My oldest brother was the only one who attended college.

97
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:16,560
Ko, you know what.

98
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:20,880
When I was in school, I…

99
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:23,440
Not attending college,

100
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,720
it’s not a big deal.

101
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:32,880
But it’s better to attend college.

102
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,720
What are you thinking?

103
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,120
Don’t make the wrong choices.

104
00:08:39,720 --> 00:08:40,200
I warn you.

105
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:42,680
I’m not doing anything.

106
00:08:42,680 --> 00:08:44,320
Of course, I will go to college.

107
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:50,560
I’m just curious why he has to work that hard.

108
00:08:51,400 --> 00:08:54,440
Why does he want to study in a difficult field
and go to college far from home?

109
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:01,160
Uncle.

110
00:09:02,520 --> 00:09:04,600
If I move away, will you be lonely?

111
00:09:06,440 --> 00:09:08,960
I think my ears would feel more comfortable.

112
00:09:09,760 --> 00:09:10,920
When are you going to leave?

113
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:12,800
I’m counting down to it.

114
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:13,920
Uncle.

115
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:23,160
I’m going to feel that something is missing.

116
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:25,200
We see each other every day.

117
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:26,960
But what can I do?

118
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,760
Everyone has to grow up.

119
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:32,880
You can’t expect them to be with you forever.

120
00:09:34,320 --> 00:09:37,120
This is how life is, Ko.

121
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:42,280
Everyone has to go on their own path to grow up.

122
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:52,000
Go on their own path to grow up?

123
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:04,440
He’s been spacing out for a while.

124
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:10,120
Uncle.

125
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,320
What if we don’t go on our own path?

126
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:18,760
What are you doing here?

127
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:25,800
We just finished the warm-up.

128
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:30,040
I’ll let you take a break before we gather again.

129
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,760
Go take a break.

130
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:33,560
Thank you.

131
00:10:35,960 --> 00:10:37,200
You forgot, didn’t you?

132
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:39,480
Forgot what?

133
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:43,000
We’re going to study for the exam together today.

134
00:10:44,040 --> 00:10:45,440
That’s right.

135
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,840
I forgot to tell you that
my coach called a practice session today.

136
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:49,400
I’m going to go to a training camp soon.

137
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:52,440
I have many things to work on in the practice today.

138
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:54,040
The practice will probably wrap up in the evening.

139
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:57,040
I can’t study with you anymore.

140
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,160
I’m sorry, Achi.

141
00:11:05,280 --> 00:11:06,920
Coach just told me yesterday evening.

142
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:09,200
When I got home, I fell asleep.

143
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,680
I forgot to call to tell you.

144
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:15,920
Aren’t you going to study?

145
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,160
The exam is coming soon.

146
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:21,360
Let me get through this period first;
I’ll find time to study with you.

147
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:24,360
I promise that I will study at home too.

148
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:27,080
You have to keep your promise.

149
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,120
Of course.

150
00:11:30,040 --> 00:11:33,680
I don’t mean to be pushy.

151
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,760
I’m just worried about you.

152
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:38,920
I want you to get into a university.

153
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,640
I don’t think that you are pushy.

154
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,600
I like it when you’re worried about me.

155
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:51,160
I’ve got to go back to the practice.

156
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:52,200
Bye.

157
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:52,600
Bye.

158
00:11:52,960 --> 00:11:53,600
You can do it.

159
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:05,120
I’m worried about Augar.

160
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,880
All he does is practice basketball.

161
00:12:10,320 --> 00:12:11,480
He probably secretly studies.

162
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:15,240
He’s studying when he’s at home, right?

163
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:18,200
Yeah.

164
00:12:21,280 --> 00:12:23,360
He’s on the national youth team now.

165
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,680
He’s still excited about it.

166
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:27,680
So he wants to put all his focus on it.

167
00:12:28,760 --> 00:12:29,840
Can you try to understand him?

168
00:12:30,680 --> 00:12:32,760
Yeah, I understand him.

169
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:39,000
I know that we all have different interests and goals.

170
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:41,600
But…

171
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,800
Doesn’t Augar want to grow up with us?

172
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:54,040
Everyone has to go on their own path to grow up.

173
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:07,840
This is how life is.

174
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:10,280
We all have to go on our own path to grow up.

175
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,320
What are you thinking?

176
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:31,240
Can you tell me?

177
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:35,400
Why do we have to grow up?

178
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:39,760
We are humans.

179
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,800
We have to grow up.

180
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,160
No, I mean…

181
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:48,680
why do we have to go on our own path?

182
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:52,640
Why do we have to go on our own path to grow up?

183
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,640
Why did you say that so casually?

184
00:14:06,920 --> 00:14:09,680
Why are you acting like going our separate ways is not a big deal?

185
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:16,160
Because it’s an inevitable reality.

186
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:18,360
We can’t be together forever.

187
00:14:20,480 --> 00:14:21,720
We have to move forward.

188
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,720
We can’t stay in the same place forever.

189
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:26,040
That’s why we have to go on our own path to grow up.

190
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:31,320
But…

191
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:33,240
don’t you want to grow up together?

192
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:39,960
Don’t you want to be together?

193
00:14:58,520 --> 00:15:01,040
Damn. I’m so sore.

194
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:04,960
You are studying for less than ten minutes.
But you already complain.

195
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:09,160
For me, studying for ten minutes is a lot.

196
00:15:15,160 --> 00:15:16,120
Damn.

197
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:17,400
What is that?

198
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:19,120
An mp3 player?

199
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:23,360
Yeah.

200
00:15:23,400 --> 00:15:25,760
Damn. I really want one.

201
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:27,200
My mom’s friend bought it for me.

202
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,000
I still don’t know how to put songs into it.

203
00:15:32,280 --> 00:15:34,400
You need to connect it to a computer.

204
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,400
Then you copy songs to the device.

205
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:37,880
Teach me how to do it.

206
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:42,720
Augar, what are you studying?

207
00:15:45,400 --> 00:15:46,240
Augar.

208
00:15:46,920 --> 00:15:47,760
Augar.

209
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,280
Augar, wake up.

210
00:15:50,280 --> 00:15:50,680
Huh?

211
00:15:51,720 --> 00:15:53,120
Wake up. You need to study.

212
00:15:53,800 --> 00:15:56,440
It’s late. Can I go back to sleep?

213
00:15:57,480 --> 00:15:59,000
I will study tomorrow.

214
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,600
You always say that.

215
00:16:00,920 --> 00:16:02,680
But you wake up late every morning.

216
00:16:03,480 --> 00:16:04,600
Not every morning.

217
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:07,320
Yesterday, I woke up at 5 a.m.

218
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:10,600
It’s because you had basketball practice.

219
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,920
What’s up with your tone?

220
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:17,280
Do you know that you are sulking?

221
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:18,400
No, I’m not sulking

222
00:16:20,160 --> 00:16:22,760
You are not sulking?

223
00:16:22,960 --> 00:16:24,120
I’m not sulking.

224
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,640
You’re so sulky.

225
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:26,800
I’m not sulky.

226
00:16:26,840 --> 00:16:27,240
Huh?

227
00:16:27,360 --> 00:16:28,120
I’m not sulky.

228
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,600
Why is this baby so sulky?

229
00:16:30,840 --> 00:16:31,160
What?

230
00:16:36,840 --> 00:16:38,440
Are you leaving?

231
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:41,760
Aren’t you going to sleep over here?

232
00:16:42,760 --> 00:16:44,080
I can’t concentrate.

233
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:45,560
I’d better go home to study.

234
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:47,720
Calm down.

235
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:49,480
Just think of this as spending time with friends.

236
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,840
Can’t we do that later?

237
00:16:53,640 --> 00:16:54,960
We are having an exam in a few days.

238
00:17:00,360 --> 00:17:01,720
Do you want to leave that much?

239
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:03,880
Orange.

240
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:43,240
Don’t get upset.

241
00:17:44,640 --> 00:17:46,080
I just want to try my best.

242
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:49,240
I want to know whether I can do it.

243
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:51,200
I…

244
00:17:52,360 --> 00:17:54,840
I don’t want to regret it when I look back.

245
00:18:09,560 --> 00:18:12,560
After the exam, everything will go back to normal.

246
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:15,680
I will have time to play with you.

247
00:18:24,200 --> 00:18:25,280
Which university will you attend?

248
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:27,240
Is it far away?

249
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:31,320
I’m not sure.

250
00:18:39,560 --> 00:18:40,680
In your future,

251
00:18:42,360 --> 00:18:43,560
will I be a part of it?

252
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:48,320
Of course.

253
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:51,120
That’s why I told you not to feel upset.

254
00:18:51,320 --> 00:18:52,040
Don’t overthink it.

255
00:18:53,680 --> 00:18:55,120
I’m not moving away.

256
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:57,720
Can you try to understand me?

257
00:19:57,480 --> 00:19:58,600
I’ll take a break.

258
00:20:10,080 --> 00:20:11,240
Achi, what are you doing here?

259
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,720
I should be the one who asks you that.

260
00:20:12,920 --> 00:20:13,960
What are you doing here?

261
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:16,000
Don’t you know we have an exam today?

262
00:20:16,480 --> 00:20:17,360
Why didn’t you take the exam?

263
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:23,560
Did you hear what I asked you?

264
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:25,480
Yes.

265
00:20:26,040 --> 00:20:29,640
But I told you I don’t need the exam to get into college.

266
00:20:29,800 --> 00:20:30,640
There’s no point in taking it.

267
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:33,360
I would have failed it anyway.

268
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:36,720
Do you really not care about it?

269
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:39,080
Don’t you care about your future?

270
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:41,240
Yes, I do. That’s why I’m practicing basketball.

271
00:20:47,160 --> 00:20:49,000
I love basketball. You know it.

272
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:51,280
Can’t you let me seriously pursue this?

273
00:20:52,360 --> 00:20:54,480
Why are you pressuring me to do those things?

274
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:57,320
Pressuring you?

275
00:21:00,280 --> 00:21:01,640
No, I mean…

276
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:04,760
I feel pressured.

277
00:21:05,480 --> 00:21:07,080
I’m not saying what you are doing is wrong.

278
00:21:07,480 --> 00:21:08,680
I just want you to understand me.

279
00:21:08,760 --> 00:21:10,040
Have you ever told me that?

280
00:21:11,120 --> 00:21:12,360
If you don’t want to do it, just say it.

281
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:14,080
Then why did you promise me?

282
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:16,200
You want me to do it, and I want to do it for you.

283
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:19,440
It doesn’t make me happy.

284
00:21:21,640 --> 00:21:23,960
I just wanted you to prepare
for the entrance exam like everyone else.

285
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,360
I want us to attend the same university.

286
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:28,040
I want us to be together just like now.

287
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,720
I want that too. Do you think I don’t want it?

288
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:32,520
But university is not my place.

289
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:40,280
Then we won’t be together.

290
00:21:57,640 --> 00:21:59,720
I do understand him, August.

291
00:22:00,960 --> 00:22:04,560
I don’t like myself being pushy like this.

292
00:22:06,080 --> 00:22:07,360
Augar doesn’t think of you that way.

293
00:22:08,120 --> 00:22:09,200
Don’t be so hard on yourself.

294
00:22:10,840 --> 00:22:13,240
But I meddled in his life.

295
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:17,240
I know that’s what he loves.

296
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:22,600
I just don’t like this feeling.

297
00:22:24,080 --> 00:22:27,800
I feel like I’m the only one who tries to do everything so we can be together.

298
00:22:30,040 --> 00:22:30,960
I get it.

299
00:22:33,800 --> 00:22:36,360
I think Augar keeps you in his mind in everything he does.

300
00:22:37,120 --> 00:22:39,800
But right now, he’s really into what he loves.

301
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:43,000
He just got an opportunity to do it.

302
00:22:45,320 --> 00:22:49,400
He likes playing basketball, but that doesn’t mean I like you any less.

303
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:58,360
He may act stupid sometimes, but he really likes you.

304
00:23:00,720 --> 00:23:03,240
Can you try to understand him?

305
00:23:06,240 --> 00:23:08,160
If basketball is his pride,

306
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:13,080
you are his best support.

307
00:23:14,080 --> 00:23:14,560
Okay?

308
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:16,640
Stop overthinking it.

309
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:36,280
Why don’t you go see Achi?

310
00:23:36,520 --> 00:23:37,280
Why did you come to see me?

311
00:23:38,400 --> 00:23:40,240
He doesn’t understand me.

312
00:23:42,640 --> 00:23:43,720
I don’t understand you either.

313
00:23:43,920 --> 00:23:45,760
You should leave. I’m going to study.

314
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:50,080
Even you are studying for the exam?

315
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:54,000
Why is everyone so serious about getting into a university?

316
00:23:54,080 --> 00:23:54,960
I can’t believe it.

317
00:23:56,160 --> 00:23:59,760
Don’t you think you need to study too,
even if you want to be an athlete?

318
00:24:00,120 --> 00:24:01,280
You can’t just neglect it.

319
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:03,800
What if you break your arm or leg?

320
00:24:04,360 --> 00:24:06,120
Then how are you going to make a living?

321
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:08,080
I know that.

322
00:24:08,360 --> 00:24:09,480
But what do you want me to do?

323
00:24:09,880 --> 00:24:12,440
Do you want me to throw this chance away
and go back to studying?

324
00:24:13,040 --> 00:24:14,120
I got into the national team.

325
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:15,200
Not everyone can do it.

326
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:17,320
What can I do to make him understand me?

327
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:32,960
Are you two also fighting?

328
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:35,040
What?

329
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:38,960
Are you fighting with Ko Song?

330
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:58,880
♪ All I can do is keep them inside an old picture ♪

331
00:25:02,960 --> 00:25:09,920
♪ And pray that we will again meet each other ♪

332
00:25:10,280 --> 00:25:13,280
♪ Wanna say "I love you" ♪

333
00:25:14,960 --> 00:25:19,400
♪ Wanna say "I love you" so you know ♪

334
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:23,920
♪ No more watching from afar, letting chances go ♪

335
00:25:24,080 --> 00:25:26,720
♪ Wanna say "I love you" so you know ♪
Ko Song. Write a message for me.

336
00:25:27,040 --> 00:25:30,040
♪ To make this worth the wait after all ♪

337
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,720
♪ “I love you” I never said ♪
Hey.

338
00:25:35,720 --> 00:25:36,080
Huh?

339
00:25:36,560 --> 00:25:38,520
It’s our last day in high school. Smile.

340
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:39,800
I’ll write you a message.

341
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:40,480
Sure.

342
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:44,600
♪ But you left without a word ♪

343
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:49,080
♪ Kept thinking, if I’d said them first ♪

344
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:51,440
♪ Things might've turned out better ♪

345
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:57,480
♪ Distance only makes me think it over ♪

346
00:25:57,480 --> 00:25:57,920
Ko.

347
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:09,560
♪ What should be said if we again meet each other ♪

348
00:26:09,760 --> 00:26:12,760
♪ Will say "I love you" ♪

349
00:26:14,320 --> 00:26:18,200
♪ Will say "I love you" so you know ♪

350
00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:22,960
♪ No more watching from afar, letting chances go ♪
GOOD LUCK, ORANGE’S OWNER

351
00:26:23,480 --> 00:26:26,080
♪ Will say "I love you" so you know ♪

352
00:26:26,320 --> 00:26:28,800
♪ To make this worth the wait after all ♪

353
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:30,360
I LOVE YOU, ORANGE.

354
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:46,120
When you were studying for the exam,

355
00:26:47,280 --> 00:26:49,080
I thought you were sucked into a book.

356
00:26:50,640 --> 00:26:51,640
You are talking nonsense.

357
00:26:52,400 --> 00:26:53,640
Everyone was doing that too.

358
00:26:58,000 --> 00:26:58,840
Can I ask you for real?

359
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:00,880
If you attend med school,

360
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:03,120
will you have to study this hard every day?

361
00:27:08,720 --> 00:27:09,920
Probably harder than this.

362
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:15,360
It’s understandable.

363
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:19,320
You want to save lives. You need to be very smart.

364
00:27:20,160 --> 00:27:22,720
All the cures are written in books.

365
00:27:24,520 --> 00:27:26,000
If you don’t read them, you won’t know.

366
00:27:28,320 --> 00:27:28,600
Ouch.

367
00:27:30,320 --> 00:27:33,000
Right now, you need to help me first.

368
00:27:33,160 --> 00:27:34,320
Orange juice got into my eye.

369
00:27:45,200 --> 00:27:46,120
So revealing.

370
00:27:48,320 --> 00:27:49,120
Don’t touch it.

371
00:27:57,360 --> 00:27:58,640
The exam result will be announced tomorrow.

372
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:00,240
Are you nervous?

373
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:01,760
Very much.

374
00:28:19,760 --> 00:28:22,240
You know that I really like you, right?

375
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:27,400
No matter what our exam results are, I still like you.

376
00:28:30,200 --> 00:28:33,680
I will find the best way so we can meet often.

377
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:35,800
Don’t worry.

378
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:36,600
Do you get it?

379
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:04,520
See you.

380
00:29:07,240 --> 00:29:07,680
See you.

381
00:29:13,560 --> 00:29:14,040
Yes.

382
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:18,120
I want to cancel the set-top box.

383
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:21,000
I’m going to move.

384
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:22,320
I don't need it anymore.

385
00:29:24,320 --> 00:29:27,040
I can’t take it with me.

386
00:29:27,040 --> 00:29:29,560
I’m going to move to another province.

387
00:29:31,520 --> 00:29:32,200
Yes, my whole family is moving.

388
00:29:49,920 --> 00:29:50,440
Damn.

389
00:29:53,640 --> 00:29:54,320
Damn.

390
00:29:54,560 --> 00:29:56,520
I got in. Augar, I got in.

391
00:29:56,520 --> 00:29:58,240
You really did it.

392
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:01,040
Call Achi.

393
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:02,680
Yeah, I’ll call and tell him.

394
00:30:03,000 --> 00:30:05,080
No, you call to ask him where he got in.

395
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:07,840
Okay, sure.

396
00:30:13,280 --> 00:30:15,440
Hello, Achi. Did you check the result?

397
00:30:16,440 --> 00:30:19,560
Damn, the faculty of medical technology.

398
00:30:20,040 --> 00:30:20,880
Which university?

399
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:24,840
So it means you and Augar
will attend different universities.

400
00:30:28,800 --> 00:30:30,040
Congratulations.

401
00:30:31,960 --> 00:30:34,400
Yes, I got into the university that I want.

402
00:30:35,880 --> 00:30:38,320
I’m going to become a Bangkokian.

403
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:42,120
I will buy a cool pair of jeans to wear.

404
00:30:43,120 --> 00:30:44,600
Sure. See you.

405
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:51,080
What’s wrong?

406
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:54,080
Nothing.

407
00:31:03,800 --> 00:31:04,680
I got in, Dad.

408
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:05,840
Really?

409
00:31:07,120 --> 00:31:08,000
Well done, my son.

410
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:11,400
I’d better call your mom.

411
00:31:13,360 --> 00:31:14,080
Honey.

412
00:31:44,680 --> 00:31:46,000
Aren’t you with Ko Song?

413
00:31:47,040 --> 00:31:48,520
He left the house in the afternoon.

414
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:50,280
He didn’t take his bike.

415
00:31:51,680 --> 00:31:52,280
Really?

416
00:32:55,040 --> 00:32:55,600
Hello.

417
00:32:56,520 --> 00:32:57,920
August, is Ko Neung with you?

418
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:02,040
What about Augar?

419
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:08,200
I called Achi.
He said Ko Neung wasn’t with him.

420
00:33:11,120 --> 00:33:11,680
Alright.

421
00:33:12,680 --> 00:33:14,160
I’ll check his house again.

422
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:30,800
Hello, Dad.

423
00:33:32,040 --> 00:33:32,600
Hello.

424
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:41,440
What’s up?

425
00:33:42,360 --> 00:33:43,440
Why do you look like that?

426
00:33:44,080 --> 00:33:44,920
Where have you been?

427
00:33:47,040 --> 00:33:48,040
I should be the one who asks you that.

428
00:33:48,040 --> 00:33:49,080
Where have you been?

429
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:51,000
Are you avoiding me?

430
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,000
Why couldn’t I find you?

431
00:33:53,040 --> 00:33:54,480
Do you know I’m really worried?

432
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:58,160
When you move away,
we won’t be seeing each other anyway.

433
00:33:58,680 --> 00:33:59,600
Why do you have to worry?

434
00:34:08,600 --> 00:34:09,840
Let’s go talk somewhere else.

435
00:34:33,160 --> 00:34:34,320
You took me here.

436
00:34:35,040 --> 00:34:35,920
What do you want to talk about?

437
00:34:40,200 --> 00:34:42,920
Are you mad
that I didn’t tell you about moving?

438
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:46,560
Weren’t you going to tell me?

439
00:34:47,040 --> 00:34:48,080
You are moving away.

440
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:51,000
Why didn’t you tell me
so I could prepare myself?

441
00:34:52,520 --> 00:34:53,760
I didn’t mean to not tell you.

442
00:34:53,920 --> 00:34:55,080
But it happened so fast.

443
00:34:56,040 --> 00:34:57,800
It happened during the exam.

444
00:34:57,880 --> 00:34:59,280
I didn’t want to fight with you then.

445
00:35:01,720 --> 00:35:02,720
You didn’t want to fight?

446
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:07,720
I needed time to prepare myself too.

447
00:35:08,520 --> 00:35:11,280
It was not easy to tell you.

448
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:13,560
So you chose not to tell me.

449
00:35:14,440 --> 00:35:15,560
How could you do this to me?

450
00:35:15,680 --> 00:35:16,800
I didn’t mean to not tell you.

451
00:35:19,960 --> 00:35:21,120
It was still uncertain back then.

452
00:35:22,040 --> 00:35:24,600
If I didn’t get into the school,
I would continue to live here.

453
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:26,760
If that was the case,

454
00:35:27,120 --> 00:35:28,760
I didn’t want to say anything to worry you.

455
00:35:39,560 --> 00:35:41,280
I got into a university in Bangkok.

456
00:35:42,720 --> 00:35:44,400
My mom wants me to move back to study there.

457
00:35:49,240 --> 00:35:51,680
Is this the reason you studied so hard?

458
00:35:53,120 --> 00:35:54,120
Have you ever thought about me?

459
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:55,760
You can’t just move here
and move away as you want.

460
00:35:56,160 --> 00:35:58,680
I want you to try to understand my reason.

461
00:35:59,320 --> 00:36:01,160
You can’t just see it
only from your perspective.

462
00:36:02,960 --> 00:36:05,840
Why don’t you just say I’m selfish?

463
00:36:07,160 --> 00:36:09,080
I just want you to try to understand me.

464
00:36:09,800 --> 00:36:11,640
I can’t make this decision alone.

465
00:36:11,920 --> 00:36:13,600
Have you ever tried to understand me?

466
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:19,720
How will I live, Ko Song?

467
00:36:21,880 --> 00:36:23,120
How will I live when you are gone?

468
00:36:23,120 --> 00:36:24,520
Do you think I’m okay with this?

469
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:28,200
Do you think I’m happy
to know that we will be apart?

470
00:36:28,680 --> 00:36:30,360
Do you think this is what I want?

471
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:31,720
But you still chose it.

472
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:33,800
You want to leave.

473
00:36:35,720 --> 00:36:38,400
Am I wrong to choose my dream?

474
00:36:39,160 --> 00:36:40,520
This is my future.

475
00:36:42,160 --> 00:36:45,280
Didn’t you say
I would be a part of your future?

476
00:36:55,240 --> 00:36:56,480
I told you.

477
00:36:58,080 --> 00:37:00,040
Nothing will change between us.

478
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:21,840
So which university did you get in?

479
00:37:22,800 --> 00:37:23,960
You don’t need to know.

480
00:37:24,720 --> 00:37:25,520
No need to be sarcastic.

481
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:30,840
I’m just doing what you did to me.

482
00:37:36,920 --> 00:37:39,440
We keep arguing the same thing.

483
00:37:40,880 --> 00:37:42,400
Do you really want me to leave, don’t you?

484
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:44,560
You are the one

485
00:37:45,520 --> 00:37:46,280
who wants to leave.

486
00:37:50,560 --> 00:37:51,160
Fine.

487
00:37:52,520 --> 00:37:53,600
Go.

488
00:37:56,360 --> 00:37:59,360
If you want to leave, then leave.

489
00:38:00,640 --> 00:38:04,280
Don’t come back if you leave.

490
00:38:04,840 --> 00:38:06,480
Fine, I’m leaving.

491
00:38:08,200 --> 00:38:09,520
Don’t ever come back.

492
00:38:10,920 --> 00:38:11,680
Go away.

493
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:12,440
Go!

494
00:39:09,400 --> 00:39:09,960
Ko.

495
00:39:22,200 --> 00:39:23,080
Are you alright?

496
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:42,760
What’s wrong?

497
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:50,200
Are you okay?

498
00:39:59,440 --> 00:40:00,640
If I were him, I would leave too.

499
00:40:01,080 --> 00:40:03,400
You were crying and whining.

500
00:40:05,400 --> 00:40:06,480
I told you everything.

501
00:40:07,520 --> 00:40:08,760
But why didn’t you take my side?

502
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:10,400
How can I take your side?

503
00:40:10,600 --> 00:40:13,480
From what I hear,
Ko Song didn’t do anything wrong.

504
00:40:14,840 --> 00:40:17,560
His only fault is not telling you about moving.

505
00:40:19,040 --> 00:40:20,680
You should have seen what I saw.

506
00:40:21,880 --> 00:40:23,280
My boyfriend was studying so hard,

507
00:40:23,920 --> 00:40:25,040
barely taking any rest.

508
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:28,160
So he can go on his path to grow up.

509
00:40:29,040 --> 00:40:31,640
He’s happy that he got in, though we will be apart.

510
00:40:33,720 --> 00:40:34,720
Am I supposed to be happy for him?

511
00:40:34,880 --> 00:40:35,720
Yes.

512
00:40:36,320 --> 00:40:38,560
Do you expect him to be with you forever?

513
00:40:39,200 --> 00:40:42,760
You want him  to throw his dream and future away.

514
00:40:43,120 --> 00:40:45,120
So he could be with you forever.

515
00:40:45,600 --> 00:40:47,760
You two would make a living from fishing.

516
00:40:47,920 --> 00:40:48,680
Is that what you want?

517
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:54,760
I understand that you are sad
about being apart from him.

518
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:57,360
But this is normal.

519
00:40:57,960 --> 00:41:00,000
You don’t need to live next door
to each other.

520
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:02,640
You don’t need to have a meal
or go to school together.

521
00:41:03,840 --> 00:41:05,800
You can still be important people
in each other’s lives.

522
00:41:10,200 --> 00:41:11,800
Which drama did you learn this from?

523
00:41:14,280 --> 00:41:17,400
I’m practicing it to tell Achi.

524
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:20,320
I knew it.

525
00:41:27,160 --> 00:41:28,920
I want you to think about it carefully.

526
00:41:30,200 --> 00:41:32,560
When you calm down,
you should go talk to him.

527
00:41:33,600 --> 00:41:36,360
He must feel hurt to hear you say that.

528
00:41:54,400 --> 00:41:55,000
Achi

529
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:58,360
I’m going to go to Tong’s shop
to get what I ordered.

530
00:41:58,800 --> 00:41:59,680
Okay, Mom.

531
00:42:18,840 --> 00:42:20,640
Augar, what are you doing here?

532
00:42:21,320 --> 00:42:23,680
Why? Do you own the market?

533
00:42:26,840 --> 00:42:28,040
Stop joking around.

534
00:42:29,040 --> 00:42:30,080
Don’t you have basketball practice?

535
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:35,640
I can’t focus on the practice
if you are still mad at me.

536
00:42:37,040 --> 00:42:38,040
I’m not mad at you.

537
00:42:39,160 --> 00:42:41,160
I’m not mad at you.

538
00:42:41,160 --> 00:42:42,200
Augar.

539
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:46,640
Are you still mad at me?

540
00:42:47,160 --> 00:42:48,840
I told you I’m not mad at you.

541
00:42:51,040 --> 00:42:52,640
Then why are you making that sour face?

542
00:42:59,080 --> 00:42:59,920
What’s wrong?

543
00:43:02,240 --> 00:43:04,520
I think I was being a jerk to you.

544
00:43:06,040 --> 00:43:07,400
I was being too pushy.

545
00:43:08,280 --> 00:43:11,840
Instead of trying to understand you,

546
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:14,840
I was acting like that toward you.

547
00:43:15,920 --> 00:43:19,160
No, I know you mean well.

548
00:43:20,800 --> 00:43:22,400
I’m still worried about you.

549
00:43:23,760 --> 00:43:25,520
I know you want to be an athlete.

550
00:43:25,920 --> 00:43:27,480
But you still need to attend university.

551
00:43:27,760 --> 00:43:29,440
Who said I wouldn’t?

552
00:43:31,160 --> 00:43:31,800
Achi.

553
00:43:32,760 --> 00:43:35,000
I got accepted to the Faculty of Sport Science
through the athlete quota.

554
00:43:35,400 --> 00:43:36,120
Really?

555
00:43:37,280 --> 00:43:38,440
Yes.

556
00:43:39,080 --> 00:43:42,080
I was going to wait until the results came out
before telling you.

557
00:43:43,040 --> 00:43:45,400
But you were mad at me.

558
00:43:45,400 --> 00:43:47,000
So I didn’t have a chance to tell you.

559
00:43:49,200 --> 00:43:50,080
And…

560
00:43:52,640 --> 00:43:54,720
you are going to attend a university far away.

561
00:43:56,400 --> 00:43:58,400
I’ll go to Bangkok to visit you often.

562
00:43:59,720 --> 00:44:00,760
Do you mean it?

563
00:44:01,160 --> 00:44:01,600
Yes.

564
00:44:02,760 --> 00:44:03,480
And…

565
00:44:07,720 --> 00:44:08,520
Let’s make up.

566
00:44:19,920 --> 00:44:21,560
Why are you here alone?

567
00:44:22,520 --> 00:44:25,240
My mom said she would go get something
and hasn’t come back.

568
00:44:28,280 --> 00:44:31,440
(Now, he is on cloud nine and smiling all day.)

569
00:44:31,920 --> 00:44:33,360
(Now, it becomes annoying.)

570
00:44:33,440 --> 00:44:35,520
It’s good that they reconciled.

571
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:37,680
He was practicing what he was going to say with me.

572
00:44:37,680 --> 00:44:38,800
It was so cheesy.

573
00:44:39,720 --> 00:44:43,800
(Anyway, are you going to see the fireworks
celebrating the MP’s birthday?)

574
00:44:46,640 --> 00:44:49,280
No, I don’t want to be in the crowd.

575
00:44:49,440 --> 00:44:50,680
I’d rather stay home.

576
00:44:52,200 --> 00:44:53,320
(It’s up to you.)

577
00:44:53,720 --> 00:44:55,480
(If you change your mind, you can call me.)

578
00:44:57,000 --> 00:44:58,360
Okay. I’m hanging up.

579
00:45:50,880 --> 00:45:52,200
What’s wrong, Ko?

580
00:45:52,440 --> 00:45:53,960
Aren’t you happy
that you got into the university?

581
00:45:55,840 --> 00:45:56,200
Huh?

582
00:45:59,120 --> 00:46:01,800
Are you okay
with me going to study in Bangkok?

583
00:46:03,600 --> 00:46:05,680
Of course.

584
00:46:05,920 --> 00:46:08,680
You got into a good university.

585
00:46:09,040 --> 00:46:10,000
Of course, I’m happy.

586
00:46:13,400 --> 00:46:14,480
Won’t you be lonely?

587
00:46:17,200 --> 00:46:19,520
Won’t you be lonely?

588
00:46:20,600 --> 00:46:23,000
But I need to adjust to it.

589
00:46:24,440 --> 00:46:31,160
I will think that you have a great opportunity
and live in a good place.

590
00:46:32,080 --> 00:46:34,280
I can endure the loneliness for it.

591
00:46:38,840 --> 00:46:40,200
Ko.

592
00:46:40,760 --> 00:46:43,280
Change is a normal part of life.

593
00:46:44,280 --> 00:46:46,560
Nothing can stay the same forever.

594
00:46:49,760 --> 00:46:52,040
You need to learn to adjust to changes.

595
00:46:56,440 --> 00:46:56,960
I’ve got to go.

596
00:46:59,440 --> 00:47:04,000
Ko Song came to see you this morning
when you were still sleeping.

597
00:47:26,200 --> 00:47:26,760
Ko.

598
00:47:29,560 --> 00:47:30,640
Your friend is here to see you.

599
00:47:31,080 --> 00:47:31,760
He’s waiting downstairs.

600
00:48:02,680 --> 00:48:03,440
We need to talk.

601
00:48:46,480 --> 00:48:47,400
I…

602
00:48:47,640 --> 00:48:48,480
I’m sorry.

603
00:48:56,080 --> 00:48:57,400
I was being selfish.

604
00:48:58,680 --> 00:48:59,680
I was acting like a child.

605
00:49:02,120 --> 00:49:06,880
I forgot that we couldn’t ride a bike
and play around forever.

606
00:49:10,280 --> 00:49:11,080
Orange.

607
00:49:13,000 --> 00:49:14,440
I should have congratulated you that day.

608
00:49:16,200 --> 00:49:17,720
Instead, I told you to go away.

609
00:49:21,200 --> 00:49:24,200
In the end, I came back to you.

610
00:49:25,960 --> 00:49:27,960
I’m such a loser.

611
00:49:34,280 --> 00:49:38,840
I heard that
you also got into a university in Bangkok.

612
00:49:44,800 --> 00:49:45,680
Congratulations.

613
00:49:49,640 --> 00:49:51,000
Aren’t you mad at me?

614
00:49:52,240 --> 00:49:53,360
Do you want to scold me back?

615
00:49:56,640 --> 00:49:57,640
Scold you about what?

616
00:49:58,560 --> 00:50:00,680
What you said was right.

617
00:50:02,800 --> 00:50:05,800
I deserved to be called selfish.

618
00:50:07,920 --> 00:50:09,880
I should have thought about your feelings.

619
00:50:11,680 --> 00:50:12,360
I’m sorry.

620
00:50:20,040 --> 00:50:21,120
I don’t like this.

621
00:50:22,480 --> 00:50:24,600
I can fight with anyone in the province.

622
00:50:25,640 --> 00:50:30,400
But your few words can hurt me badly.

623
00:50:34,040 --> 00:50:37,560
Are you that sad that
one of your gang members will be away?

624
00:50:42,320 --> 00:50:44,560
You are my favorite member.

625
00:50:46,800 --> 00:50:49,080
Yes, I know I was wrong.

626
00:50:49,520 --> 00:50:50,440
I regret what I did.

627
00:50:55,640 --> 00:50:56,400
So…

628
00:50:57,480 --> 00:50:58,520
you are not mad at me anymore, right?

629
00:50:58,840 --> 00:51:01,080
What? What do you mean?

630
00:51:01,080 --> 00:51:02,400
Do you want to get mad again?

631
00:51:02,880 --> 00:51:04,520
You’re going to be a college boy soon.

632
00:51:04,720 --> 00:51:06,400
Why are you still acting like a child?

633
00:51:06,560 --> 00:51:09,120
Hey, how could you say that to me?

634
00:51:09,120 --> 00:51:11,040
I’ll teach you a lesson.

635
00:51:11,280 --> 00:51:12,840
I’ll tickle you because you can’t stand it.

636
00:51:14,560 --> 00:51:16,080
I’ll teach you a lesson.

637
00:51:16,760 --> 00:51:17,560
Don’t tickle me.

638
00:51:27,880 --> 00:51:29,200
Can I ask you something?

639
00:51:30,600 --> 00:51:31,400
What?

640
00:51:38,240 --> 00:51:39,400
Can we not be apart?

641
00:51:44,000 --> 00:51:45,440
No matter where we are,

642
00:51:46,360 --> 00:51:47,440
we will never be apart.

643
00:51:50,320 --> 00:51:51,360
Can you do that, Ko Song?

644
00:51:58,200 --> 00:52:00,280
We will never be apart.

645
00:52:07,840 --> 00:52:08,720
I promise.

646
00:52:27,320 --> 00:52:31,000
(Many things happened
before we graduated high school.)

647
00:52:31,640 --> 00:52:35,120
(The thing we were most sensitive about  was changes.)

648
00:52:38,120 --> 00:52:42,120
(Changes made us anxious and scared.)

649
00:52:42,560 --> 00:52:44,440
(It led to a misunderstanding between us.)

650
00:52:45,680 --> 00:52:52,080
(But changes helped us learn and love each other more.)

651
00:52:55,920 --> 00:52:56,560
(Hello?)

652
00:52:57,360 --> 00:52:59,240
(Honey, did you fall asleep?)

653
00:53:01,800 --> 00:53:06,720
(We stop guessing, focusing,
or worrying about what will happen in the future.)

654
00:53:12,080 --> 00:53:16,280
(It’s useless to worry about things that haven’t happened yet.)

655
00:53:19,400 --> 00:53:20,760
(It’s wasting our time together.)

656
00:53:34,280 --> 00:53:37,600
♪ Even when winter fades I’ll still wait on ♪

657
00:53:37,840 --> 00:53:41,240
♪ Till the final raindrop falls, hope is never gone ♪

658
00:53:41,320 --> 00:53:45,760
♪ As long as I have you holding my hand
as we walk on ♪

659
00:53:46,280 --> 00:53:47,880
♪ I fear nothing if this season has you ♪

660
00:53:47,880 --> 00:53:52,840
(We should be focusing on the present
that is beautiful and shining.)

661
00:53:53,240 --> 00:53:56,960
(It’s the most precious moment in the 18 years of our lives.)

